    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="800"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d800">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.48/36: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 9, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your 123, September 27, 2 p.m. In a letter which Rabbi Silver has addressed to
                    the Chairman of the American Red Cross the statement is made that you have
                    informed Kaplan<note n="54" xml:id="d800fn54">Elizer Kaplan, Financial Director
                        of the Jewish Agency in Palestine.</note> that on September 27 you had
                    cabled the Department as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Palestine Jewry is faced with a real financial emergency in its efforts
                            to meet various war-born problems, the absorption of indigent <pb
                                facs="0889" n="877" xml:id="pg_877"/> refugees, and unemployment
                            resulting from economic dislocation as well as those of air-raid
                            precautions, possible urban evacuation, medical aid and direct relief
                            for air-raid victims.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>In as much as no such passage appears in your telegram under reference please
                    telegraph the facts in order that the Department may be in a position to comment
                    on the statement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
